            "prompt": "I need to implement a fix for ledger issue #1941, which is about warnings when a commodity format is declared and then amounts with higher precision are used.\n\n## Issue Summary\nWhen a user declares a commodity format (e.g., `commodity USD\\n  format 1,000.00 USD`), this sets the `COMMODITY_STYLE_NO_MIGRATE` flag which locks the display precision. However, if a transaction has an amount with more decimal places than declared (e.g., `1.98547473 USD` when format says 2 decimal places), there's no warning - it silently displays with less precision.\n\n## Current Code Understanding\n\nIn `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-1941/src/textual_xacts.cc`, around line 549-586, amounts are parsed from transaction postings:\n```cpp\nif (next && *next && (*next != ';' && *next != '=')) {\n    // ...\n    if (*next != '(') // indicates a value expression\n        (void)post->amount.parse(stream, PARSE_NO_REDUCE);\n    else\n        parse_amount_expr(stream, *context.scope, *post.get(), post->amount, ...);\n    \n    if (!post->amount.is_null() && post->amount.has_commodity()) {\n        // ... existing code for annotations, fixed rates, etc.\n    }\n}\n```\n\nAfter amount parsing:\n- `post->amount.precision()` = the parsed precision (e.g., 8 for `1.98547473 USD`)\n- `post->amount.commodity().precision()` = the locked declared format precision (e.g., 2 for `format 1,000.00 USD`)\n- When `COMMODITY_STYLE_NO_MIGRATE` is set on the commodity, the commodity's precision was NOT updated during parsing\n\nThe `COMMODITY_STYLE_NO_MIGRATE` flag is defined in `/Users/johnw/src/ledger/fix-1941/src/commodity.h`:\n```cpp\n#define COMMODITY_STYLE_NO_MIGRATE 0x2000  ///< Do not migrate formatting from parsed amounts.\n```\n\nThis flag is set by:\n1. `commodity_format_directive()` in `textual_directives.cc` - when `commodity X\\n  format ...` is used\n2. `default_commodity_directive()` in `textual_directives.cc` - when `D X.XX COMM` is used\n\nThe `context.warning()` method can emit a warning with file/line context. It's used in other places like:\n```cpp\ncontext.warning(_f(\"Unknown payee '%1%'\") % payee);\n```\n\n## Requested Change\n\nAdd a warning in `textual_xacts.cc` inside the `if (!post->amount.is_null() && post->amount.has_commodity())` block. When:\n1. `post->amount.commodity().has_flags(COMMODITY_STYLE_NO_MIGRATE)` is true (format was declared)\n2. `post->amount.precision() > post->amount.commodity().precision()` (amount has more decimals than declared)\n\nEmit a warning: `\"Amount for commodity 'X' has N decimal places but declared format only shows M\"`\n\nPlease:\n1. Read the relevant files first\n2. Add the warning check in the right place in `textual_xacts.cc`\n3. Create a regression test in `test/regress/1941.test` that demonstrates the warning behavior\n\nThe test should:\n- Declare a commodity format with limited precision (e.g., 2 decimal places)\n- Have a transaction with an amount exceeding that precision\n- Use `__ERROR__` in the test to verify the warning appears in stderr\n\nRemember the test file format from CLAUDE.md - use `__ERROR__` for expected stderr output within a test block.\n\nIMPORTANT: Do not commit the changes, just make the edits.\n",
